00:34:55.280 --> 00:34:57.040
or getting in touch with people?

00:34:57.040 --> 00:34:59.775
What would be some of
the first couple of steps

00:34:59.775 --> 00:35:01.390
to getting into sponsorships?

00:35:01.390 --> 00:35:04.085
ELLEN GUNNING: To actually find
something that's sponsoring,

00:35:04.085 --> 00:35:05.340
I would go the other
way around with it.

00:35:05.340 --> 00:35:07.506
If you're not from Ireland,
I would choose something

00:35:07.506 --> 00:35:09.350
that was unique to you.

00:35:09.350 --> 00:35:11.621
So it might be Brazilian
movies or something.

00:35:11.621 --> 00:35:12.990
And you think, OK.

00:35:12.990 --> 00:35:14.990
Have a look at the
community and see where

00:35:14.990 --> 00:35:16.190
is there a community week?

00:35:16.190 --> 00:35:18.189
And if there's a community
week, is there a role

00:35:18.189 --> 00:35:19.857
in there somewhere for movies?

00:35:19.857 --> 00:35:22.190
And as part of the movies,
we can show Brazilian movies.

00:35:22.190 --> 00:35:23.660
It depends on what
the connection

00:35:23.660 --> 00:35:25.370
is that you're trying to make.

00:35:25.370 --> 00:35:26.671
But it also sets you up.

00:35:26.671 --> 00:35:27.920
You're the logical connection.

00:35:27.920 --> 00:35:29.660
So you can actually
introduce yourself and say,

00:35:29.660 --> 00:35:29.990
I'm Brazilian.

00:35:29.990 --> 00:35:31.975
That's why I'm passionate
about Brazilian movies.

00:35:31.975 --> 00:35:32.750
You never would've guessed.

00:35:32.750 --> 00:35:34.210
And people will go,
oh, is that why?

00:35:34.210 --> 00:35:35.450
Because people won't
make a connection

00:35:35.450 --> 00:35:36.324
unless you tell them.

00:35:36.324 --> 00:35:37.445
That's the other thing.

00:35:37.445 --> 00:35:39.020
They will say you're an
"ex-pat," or whatever.

00:35:39.020 --> 00:35:41.353
You're not Irish, but they
won't know where you're from.

00:35:41.353 --> 00:35:44.110
So I would look for something
that is close to your heart,

00:35:44.110 --> 00:35:47.340
that you're an expert in,
that you can offer to sponsor.

00:35:47.340 --> 00:35:48.140
But it's more work.

00:35:48.140 --> 00:35:50.890
It means that you need to set
it up, create it, and run it.

00:35:50.890 --> 00:35:53.210
But if you do, people will come.

00:35:53.210 --> 00:35:55.960
When I did the first
Active Age week,

00:35:55.960 --> 00:35:58.095
everybody told me that
I was wasting my time.

00:35:58.095 --> 00:35:59.720
And if I was looking
at creating things

00:35:59.720 --> 00:36:02.971
for senior citizens, what they
were interested in was bingo.

00:36:02.971 --> 00:36:04.091
So if I did bingo--

00:36:04.091 --> 00:36:04.590
[LAUGHTER]

00:36:04.590 --> 00:36:04.830
Honest to God.

00:36:04.830 --> 00:36:07.204
So if I did bingo seven nights
a week, they'd be happier.

00:36:07.204 --> 00:36:08.620
And I said, look at this face.

00:36:08.620 --> 00:36:11.030
Does this look like a face
that ever played bingo?

00:36:11.030 --> 00:36:14.190
Or has any desire to
create bingo nights?

00:36:14.190 --> 00:36:15.190
Not happening.

00:36:15.190 --> 00:36:17.273
But what I will do, is
I'll do one night of bingo.

00:36:17.273 --> 00:36:18.940
But I will do everything
else around it.

00:36:18.940 --> 00:36:20.981
And if nobody comes to
anything, there's my butt.

00:36:20.981 --> 00:36:23.357
You can kick it and say, I
told you, you're [INAUDIBLE]..

00:36:23.357 --> 00:36:23.981
You were wrong.

00:36:23.981 --> 00:36:25.220
And we did historical nights.

00:36:25.220 --> 00:36:27.140
We did boat trips.

00:36:27.140 --> 00:36:29.875
We did mystery trips
out into the country.

00:36:29.875 --> 00:36:32.173
We did afternoons where
people just came in

00:36:32.173 --> 00:36:34.040
and somebody played
piano and they all sang.

00:36:34.040 --> 00:36:36.012
We were blocked out
every single night.

00:36:36.012 --> 00:36:37.220
There was standing room only.

00:36:37.220 --> 00:36:38.630
At every single function.

00:36:38.630 --> 00:36:40.911
And they all turned
up for bingo as well.

00:36:40.911 --> 00:36:43.160
But nobody said at the end
of the week, what a pity it

00:36:43.160 --> 00:36:44.240
wasn't all bingo.

00:36:44.240 --> 00:36:46.670
So I think if you
actually find something

00:36:46.670 --> 00:36:49.130
that you're passionate
about, that you can create,

00:36:49.130 --> 00:36:51.670
people will come, and it
will make the association.

00:36:51.670 --> 00:36:54.056
It also give you a niche
that nobody else has.

00:36:54.056 --> 00:36:55.880
The other thing
with sponsorship is,

00:36:55.880 --> 00:36:58.700
if you come in to sponsor
after somebody has been there,

00:36:58.700 --> 00:37:01.970
it takes a long time to lose
the last sponsor's name.

00:37:01.970 --> 00:37:05.700
So the general rule is that if
you're doing a sponsorhip deal,

00:37:05.700 --> 00:37:07.270
it should be for three years.

00:37:07.270 --> 00:37:08.750
And you should an extra two.

00:37:08.750 --> 00:37:10.980
So you've a facility that
nobody else can step in

00:37:10.980 --> 00:37:11.688
for the next two.

00:37:11.688 --> 00:37:13.032
You get first dibs on it.

00:37:13.032 --> 00:37:15.841
But after five, you should move
on and inspect your audience

00:37:15.841 --> 00:37:16.340
again.

00:37:16.340 --> 00:37:19.160
Because after five, if you're
targeting 17-year-olds,

00:37:19.160 --> 00:37:21.747
the 17-year-olds are
now 18, 19, 20, or 22.

00:37:21.747 --> 00:37:24.249
They're no longer interested
in the same things.

00:37:24.249 --> 00:37:25.665
They've moved onto
something else.

00:37:25.665 --> 00:37:29.200
But after five years, your
name stays for at least two.

00:37:29.200 --> 00:37:31.730
So the next sponsor
coming in has an awful job

00:37:31.730 --> 00:37:34.310
branding their name onto
whatever it is they're doing.

00:37:34.310 --> 00:37:37.401
So I'd go the other route, and
create it with your name on it

00:37:37.401 --> 00:37:38.754
and let them follow you.

